# Collaborate on reports

<head>
  <title>Collaborate and Share W&B Reports</title>
</head>

Once you have saved a report, you can select the **Share** button to collaborate. A draft copy of the report is created when you select the **Edit** button. Draft reports auto-save. Select **Save to report** to publish your changes to the shared report.

A warning notification will appear if an edit conflict occurs. This can occur if you and another collaborator edit the same report at the same time. The warning notification will guide you to resolve potential edit conflicts.

![Report sharing modal for a report in a 'Public' project](@site/static/images/reports/share-report.gif)

### Comment on reports

Click the comment button on a panel in a report to add a comment directly to that panel.

![Adding a comment to a panel](/images/reports/demo_comment_on_panels_in_reports.gif)



### Who can edit and share reports?

Reports that are created within an individual's private project is only visible to that user. The user can share their project to a team or to the public.

On team projects, both the administrator, or member who created the report, can toggle permissions between edit or view access for other team members. Team members can share reports.

To share a report, select the **Share** button on the upper right hand corner.  You can either provide an email account or copy the magic link. Users invited by email will need to log into Weights & Biases to view the report. Users who are given a magic link to not need to log into Weights & Biases to view the report.

Shared reports are view-only.

QUESTION: 
Hi Wandbot, I'm using a free account. I want to share my existing personal project with others but I couldn't find the option you mentioned before. Can you show me step by step how to do it?

ANSWER:
To share your existing personal project with others, you can follow these steps:

1. Open your project's settings page.
2. Look for the "Owners" section, where you can see the current owner of the project.
3. If the owner is set to your personal account, you will need to create a team first. To create a team, click on the "Teams" tab in the navigation menu and select "Create New Team". Follow the instructions to create the team.
4. Once you have created the team, go back to your project's settings page.
5. In the "Owners" section, click on the dropdown menu and select the team you created as the new owner.
6. Save the changes.
7. Now, your existing personal project is shared with others through the team you created.

Please note that this feature may not be available in the free account. If you still couldn't find the option, please check if you have access to team features with your current account level.

QUESTION: Hi, I created a report in my private project, but I am unable to share it with my team members. How can I share a report created within my individual private project with my team?

ANSWER: 
To share a report that you created within your individual private project with your team members, you need to follow these steps:

1. Open the report you want to share.
2. In the upper right-hand corner of the report, click on the "Share" button.
3. A sharing modal will appear. Here, you can choose to either provide an email account or copy the magic link.
   - If you choose to provide an email account, the user you invite will need to log into Weights & Biases to view the report.
   - If you choose to copy the magic link, the user you share it with will not need to log into Weights & Biases to view the report.
4. After selecting your preferred sharing option, click on the "Share" button in the sharing modal.

Note: Shared reports are view-only, meaning that your team members will not be able to edit the report. Only the administrator or the member who created the report can toggle permissions between edit or view access for other team members.

QUESTION: Hi, I'm using a free account and I want to share my existing project with others. I tried to move it to a team as you instructed, but couldn't find the option. Can you show me how to share my project step-by-step?

ANSWER:
To share your existing project with others, follow these steps:

1. Select the project you want to share from your project list.
2. On the project's settings page, look for the "Owner" section.
3. In the "Owner" section, you will see an option to change the owner to a team you created. Click on it.
4. Choose the team you want to transfer the ownership to from the dropdown menu.
5. After selecting the team, click on the "Save Changes" button to save the ownership transfer.

Once you have transferred the ownership of your project to the team, it will be shared with the members of that team. They will be able to access and collaborate on the project.

If you are still unable to find the option to change the owner to a team, please make sure you have the necessary permissions and that you are logged in to the correct account. If you continue to face issues, reach out to the Weights & Biases support team for further assistance.
